      <section eId="sec_1217">
        <num>1217</num>
        <heading>Commissions</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_1217__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A receiver shall be entitled, in addition to his necessary\nexpenses, to such commissions upon the sums received and disbursed as\nmay be allowed by the court, as follows:\n</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="sec_1217__subsec_a__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>On the first twenty thousand dollars, not exceeding five percent;\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_1217__subsec_a__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>On the next eighty thousand dollars, not exceeding two and\none-half percent; and\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_1217__subsec_a__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>On the remainder, not exceeding one percent.\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1217__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>If the commissions of the receiver so computed do not amount to\none hundred dollars, the court in its discretion may allow such sum not\nexceeding one hundred dollars as shall be reasonable.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1217__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>When more than one receiver shall be appointed, the compensation\nherein provided shall be divided between them, as the court directs.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
